eressant, die sich für eine kultursoziologische Erklärung des Tourismus sowie für eine empirisch gesättigte Theorie des Authentischen interessieren.  aWhat meaning does tourism have for society today? Departing from the thesis of »staged authenticity« (MacCannell), and by way of touristic case studies, Robert Schäfer sounds out the role that tourism plays in contemporary society, and the meaning of authenticity in this context.Through the entanglement of empirical research and theoretical construction of concepts, the study is of interest for anybody who is interested in a cultural-sociological explanation of tourism and an empirically satisfying theory of the authentic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAuthentizität. 4aBildanalyse. 4aKultur. 4aKultursoziologie. 4aReisen. 4aReligionssoziologie. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aStaged Authenticity. 4aTextanalyse. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAuthenticity.  aCulture.  aImage Analysis.  aSociological Theory.  aSociology of Culture.  aSociology of Religion.  aSociology.  aStaged Authenticity.  aText Analysis.  aTravelling.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2014z9783110370416oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839427446zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839427446423C